stories.text:
HSV has recently been linked to Alzheimer's and other degenerative diseases.

Today I was speaking to an activist on Reddit that advocating a cure for HSV-1 / HSV-2. There's promising work being done in the field namely by Dr. Keith Jerome and Fred Hutch and a Chinese Pharmaceutical company BD Gene.

These companies are working on a therapeutic vaccine that could help cure the 2/3s of the US population from the disease. What would it take to find and reach out to investors or philanthropist to help fund these types of works.

The market for a cure is lucrative no doubt, are there any organisations out there that would donate purely based on a philanthropist nature?
